cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

The paper deals with computer vision-based gait recognition using deep learning-based algorithms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of Long-Short Term Memory networks, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The paper also involves the evaluation of the proposed algorithm on public datasets, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper deals with occlusion handling strategies, which is a common problem in computer vision and falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
